summary:
Back in my teens using a dial-up modem with (what seemed to be decent) connection speeds of 56Kbps, I would scour search engines for ‘floor plans’, print(!!) them out and start imagining what it would be like going through the spaces. That is where my entry into the world of architecture and design began. 

Today I am an Architect and Co-Founder at vellum.ink, where we are revolutionising architecture through generative design, allowing both property developers and architects to rapidly test options and assess the viability of development sites. 

At vellum, I am involved with research, strategy and user testing, working closely with my co-founders to bring the vision to life in an intuitive and meaningful way. We have just received our first investment round and are on track to make a big impact in the world of architecture. 

I am all for knowledge exchange and the sharing of ideas, and if you’d like to connect or find out more, please reach out!
